Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine light buff-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Eudoxos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0364.09 and BM 1989,0710.29.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Trimming points to provenance)
